article.headline: No. 11 Texas A&M rides Gant's 28 to cruise past New Orleans
article.linkText: Gant leads No. 11 Texas A&M past New Orleans
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Danielle Gant scored a career-high 28 points and pulled down 14 rebounds Sunday to lead No. 12 Texas A&M to a 73-44 victory over New Orleans.

Gant shot 10-of-12 from the field and 8-of-9 from the free-throw line for the Aggies, who won their fifth straight and their 22nd straight home game. Gant also had three blocked shots.

La Toya Micheaux scored 11 points, including seven of Texas A&M's first 13, and Takia Starks added 10.

Texas A&M (8-1) led 37-25 at the half.

Jada Frazier came off the bench to score 19 points to lead New Orleans (5-4). Brittany Helm had nine points, including seven in the first half.
